                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        <customfield id="customfield_12310183" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Steps to Reproduce</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&lt;p&gt;To reproduce use a fresh server installation.&lt;br/&gt;
In standalone mode it still work with the following CLI:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/subsystem=transactions:write-attribute(name=node-identifier,value=&quot;$&lt;/p&gt;
{txNodeIdentifier}&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
/system-property=txNodeIdentifier:add(value=main)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In domain mode this CLI commands are used:&lt;br/&gt;
/host=master/server-config=server-one/system-property=txNodeIdentifier:add(value=one)&lt;br/&gt;
/host=master/server-config=server-two/system-property=txNodeIdentifier:add(value=two)&lt;br/&gt;
/profile=full/subsystem=transactions:write-attribute(name=node-identifier,value=&quot;${txNodeIdentifier}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after restart the server fail with the error.&lt;br/&gt;
Also the CLI script from a quickstart can be used:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wfink/quickstart/blob/master/ejb-multi-server/install-domain.cli&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/wfink/quickstart/blob/master/ejb-multi-server/install-domain.cli&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</customfieldvalue>

                        </customfieldvalues>
                    </customfield>
